metadata:
  section_id: 27
  section_name: Chapter 27
  hadith_first: 183
  hadith_last: 189

hadiths[7]{hadithnumber,text,grades,reference,international_number,narrator_chain,chapter_intro}:
183,"""We were in the home of the Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) one day, and he served a meal. I had never seen a meal from which greater blessing was obtained at the beginning of our eating, nor less blessing at the end of it, so we said: 'O Messenger of Allah, how is this?' He said: 'We mentioned the Name of Allah when we ate. Then someone who ate sat down and did not pronounce the Name of Allah (Exalted is He), so Satan ate with him!’”",,,48898,"Abu Ayyub Al-Ansari said:",Chapter 27
184,"“Allah’s Messenger said (Allah bless him and give him peace): ‘If one of you eats and forgets to mention Allah (Exalted is He) during his meal, let him say: B'ismillah awwalahu wa akhirahu, which means, 'In the name of Allah at its beginning and at its end'.”",,,48899,"'A’isha said:",Chapter 27
185,"'O my dear son, pronounce\nthe Name of Allah(Exalted is He), eat with your right hand, and eat what is directly in front of you!’”",,,48900,"'Umar ibn Abi Salama said that he went in to see Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace), who had a meal before him, so he said to him:",Chapter 27
186,"“Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) used to say, when he had finished his meal: ‘Praise be to Allah, who has fed us and quenched our thirst, and has made us Muslims'!”",,,48901,"Abu Sa‘id al-Khudri said:",Chapter 27
187,"“When the table was removed from in front of him, Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) used to say: ‘Much fine blessed praise to Allah! It is neither the last of our food, nor can it be dispensed with, O our Lord'!”",,,48902,"Abu Umama said:",Chapter 27
188,"""The Prophet (Allah bless him and give him peace) was eating with six of his Companions, when a Bedouin came and devoured it in two mouthfuls, so Allah’s Messenger said (Allah bless him and give him peace): 'If he had invoked the Name of Allah, it would have been enough for you all'!”",,,48903,"'Aisha said:",Chapter 27
189,"""Allah’s Messenger said (Allah bless him and give him peace): 'Allah is surely well pleased with the servant’s eating and praising Him for the food, or drinking and praising Him for the drink'!”",,,48904,"Anas ibn Malik said:",Chapter 27
